HEADWORD: Subovate
<hw>Sub*o"vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Nearly in the form
of an egg, or of the section of an egg, but having the inferior
extremity broadest; nearly ovate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subovated</ent>⟦br⟧
